Item from and after all my just debts, my aforesaid Legacies, funeral expenses and other incident charges in and about the probate of this my Will shall be paid off and discharged, I give and bequeath all the rest and residue of moneys, securities for money, goods, chattels and personal estate whatso- ever and wheresoever be it of what nature or kind soever unto my said son Joseph Tucker and to his Executors administrators and assigns for ever. Item I nominate and appoint my said sons Samuel Jeake and Joseph Tucker joynt executors of this my will and Lastly I do hereby revoke all former and other wills by me at any time heretofore made and do declare this to be my last Will and Testament In Witness whereof I the said Elizabeth Tucker have to this my last Will and Testament written and contained in these two sheets of paper to the first sheet I have sett my name and to this last sheet my name and seal dated the day and year first before written Elisa Tucker. Signed, sealed, pub- lished and declared by the said Testatrix for and as her last Will and Testament in the presence of us who have in the said Testatrixes presence subscribed our names as Witnesses the words [thereof two pillows and white quilt] being first underlined. Ann Burton, William Wybourn, Edwin Wardroper.

This Will was proved at London the twenty third day of July in the year of our Lord one thousand seven hundred and thirty six before the Right Worshipfull John Bettesworth Doctor of Laws Master Keeper or Commissary of the Prerogative Court of Canterbury lawfully constituted by the Oaths of Samuel Jeake and Joseph Tucker Executors named in the said Will to whom administration of all and singular the Goods Chattels and Credits of the deceased was granted being first sworn by Commission duly to administer.
